about.description:
Waitress is meant to be a production-quality pure-Python WSGI server with
very acceptable performance. It has no dependencies except ones which live
in the Python standard library. It runs on CPython on Unix and Windows under
Python 2.7+ and Python 3.3+. It is also known to run on PyPy 1.6.0+ on UNIX.
It supports HTTP/1.0 and HTTP/1.1.

Waitress is meant to be a production-quality pure-Python WSGI server with
very acceptable performance. It has no dependencies except ones which live

name: waitress
raw_meta_yaml:
{% set name = "waitress" %}
{% set version = "2.1.2" %}

package:
  name: {{ name|lower }}
  version: {{ version }}

source:
  url: https://pypi.io/packages/source/{{ name[0] }}/{{ name }}/{{ name }}-{{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: 780a4082c5fbc0fde6a2fcfe5e26e6efc1e8f425730863c04085769781f51eba

build:
  noarch: python
  number: 0
  script: {{ PYTHON }} -m pip install . -vv
  entry_points:
    - waitress-serve = waitress.runner:run

requirements:
  host:
    - python >=3.6
    - pip
  run:
    - python >=3.6

test:
  imports:
    - waitress
  commands:
    - waitress-serve --help

about:
  home: https://github.com/Pylons/waitress
  license: ZPL-2.0
  license_family: OTHER
  license_file: LICENSE.txt
  summary: Production-quality pure-Python WSGI server
  description: |
    Waitress is meant to be a production-quality pure-Python WSGI server with
    very acceptable performance. It has no dependencies except ones which live
    in the Python standard library. It runs on CPython on Unix and Windows under
    Python 2.7+ and Python 3.3+. It is also known to run on PyPy 1.6.0+ on UNIX.
    It supports HTTP/1.0 and HTTP/1.1.
  doc_url: http://docs.pylonsproject.org/projects/waitress/en/latest/
  dev_url: https://github.com/Pylons/waitress

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - carlodri
    - xhochy
